<D>__{i helped you buy it. it came with two pairs of pants. it's for luck, johnny. when you propose marriage to a woman, you should kneel down.}
<C>__{mr. johnny}
<D>__{alright.}
<A>__{mr. johnny slowly gets out of his chair. there's not enough room for him to kneel down. he has to ask two off duty pro wrestlers who are eating dinner to move their chairs. they do so with bemused expressions. their names are bob and mook.}
<B>__{shy waiter brings perry a fresh glass of vodka asks the shy waiter}
<C>__{perry}
<D>__{is that man praying?}
<B>__{mr. johnny on his knees addresses loretta}
<C>__{johnny}
<D>__{so. will you ma...}
